text: Eri Hozumi and Zhang Shuai were the defending champions, but Zhang chose to compete in Nanchang instead. Hozumi played alongside Makoto Ninomiya, but lost in the quarterfinals to Christina McHale and Valeria Savinykh. Misaki Doi and Nao Hibino won the title, defeating McHale and Savinykh in the final, 3–6, 6–4, [10–4]. ==Seeds== ==Draw== ===Draw=== ==References== *Draw Japan Women's Open - Women's Doubles 2019 Women's Doubles
